First Gating Criteria Released for Reno County Schools

USD 312 Haven has received its first guidance from the Reno County Health Department related to "Gating Criteria". This criteria uses reno county data to help guide and direct schools related to which learning plan will be used for the following week. We are happy to report that although our gating will move to the yellow zone, (See USD 312 Gating Criteria) our learning platform will continue to be "in-person" just as we have been using in the past 2 weeks. The number of positive cases has actually decreased slightly for Reno County. We hope this trend continues. You can plan to receive a notification each Friday outlining the following weeks learning plan. Please continue to follow all health guidelines being provided by the Reno County Health Department.

Gating Criteria:
https://core-docs.s3.amazonaws.com/documents/asset/uploaded_file/914174/Reno_County_Gating_Criteria-_USD_312_Haven_-_Sheet1.pdf

Any questions can be sent to our Food Service Director, Sheree Jones, sjones@havenschools.com.

HGS is READY for Compact day!
Due to COVID we have moved outside. Please meet your teacher at your assigned time at their table located in front of their general grade level area on either the south or west side of the building.

Principal Scott

post_text: To parents of students riding buses. All passengers will be required to wear a face mask when riding in a school bus or any school vehicle. In addition, all passengers will have their temperature taken prior to being transported. If their temperature is above 100.0, they will not be transported. I ask that you take your student's temperature before sending them to the bus to help prevent them from being sent home, and to make sure young students have an adult available to receive them if they are running a fever. If there is a medical reason your student cannot wear a mask, please contact transportation at 620-465-3445 ext 1110 or email mbray@havenschools.com Thank you,

post_text:
Haven High School Class of 2020 and USD 312 community:

I wanted to send a communication to everyone to mind you of our plans for Haven High School graduation. As stated before, through monitoring current levels of COVID-19 infection and consulting with the Reno County Health Department, it has been determined that graduation will be held outdoors at the Haven High School Stadium Saturday 18th, at 9:00 am.

We are increasing social distancing opportunities. Patrons are welcome to sit in the stands or bring lawn chairs and increase social distance to their preference. Audience members are free to place lawn chairs on the track but asked to refrain from being on the football field or blocking any sidewalks used for ADA purposes. Audience members are also encouraged to bring water for hydration. Please be aware of Reno County COVID-19 mask mandates.

Graduates will need to report to the gym at 8:15 am.

Inclement Weather: If the weather does not allow the event to take place on Saturday 18th it will be moved to Sunday at 7 PM.

post_text:
Attention parents of students at Haven Grade School. The district will be providing our first ever Virtual Parent Camp on Tuesday, May 6 at 6pm. The purpose is to address two issues- 1) Engaging your children at home in the continuous learning plan and 2) Supporting your children's social/emotional needs during this time. Teachers will provide suggestions and ideas on how to serve your children during this time. Parents will then be asked to share ideas with one another in a zoom conference room. Participants will need access to a computer with a microphone and camera. To sign up use this link:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1G2PxjdT6Xyl0jbLU2gnQ5HQBaoKA5jqFQvQOYCJLiZY/edit

One we receive your sign up we will send the zoom link for you to register and receive the link to use on Tuesday evening.

post_text:
USD 312 is SO PROUD to say that our Food Service Program has been recognized as April's FSO (Food Service Operation) of the Month!

We are incredibly thankful to all of our lunch staff for providing the best lunches to our students. Not only are the meals delicious and nutritious, our staff worked hard to provide more meal options everyday!

Implemented at the middle school and high school level, students now have the option to "order ahead". A new way to keep student involved in their lunch choices and to minimize food waste.

This is an incredible accomplishment! #USD312Proud

USD 312 has been working to create an easier way to stay in touch with parents and our community. In an attempt to stay connected, we are building our social media platform and providing Facebook pages for each of our school buildings. From this point forward, we will be using our newly created Facebook pages to keep you up to date on each school's activities. Make sure to LIKE and FOLLOW each page if you would like to stay up to date on a particular school! We hope that this will make it easier for you to stay informed! Please share this post for others to see!

post_text: If any upcoming 9th graders are interested in law enforcement, the Hutchinson Police Department is offering a free, one-day youth academy on June 18th!
shared_text:
Hutchinson Police Department
May 22, 2019 at 9:25 AM ¬∑

YOUTH ACADEMY
The Hutchinson Police Department is holding a one-day youth academy for students entering 9th grade this next school year, it will be held on June 18th. The youth academy is for students who are interested in law enforcement or just want a better understanding of what we do and want to get a more hands on experience. The academy is a full day that is free to the participant and lunch will be provided.
Application packets are available at the police department or you can email thad.pickard@renolec.com for more information or to get the application packet. There is a waiver that needs to be notarized, but our supervisors are notaries and we can get that done for free. We are always excited to be involved with our young people and we believe that this will be a fun and exciting way to interact with the future of our community. Slots for the academy are limited, but if there is enough interest, we will open up other dates this summer.

post_text: Yesterday marked the beginning of new adventures. Haven USD 312 celebrated 6 wonderful teachers who, after giving years of love and hard work to our schools, have decided to start a new journey and enjoy retirement. Robbie Hays, Annette Mathias, Sandra Schmidt, Lisa Vierthaler, Dawna Rein, and Lynn Mowder have given their dedication to students, touched countless lives, established unforgettable friendships, and created everlasting memories. USD 312 is incredibly thankful for each of these teachers and the positive impact they have left in our district. You will be greatly missed!!
